Intermediaries are required to prepare and provide a daily account statement for each client, which must include the following information:  

(a) The name under which the intermediary and its associated entities operate their business;  

(b) The client’s name, address, and account number;  

(c) The date on which the statement is prepared;  

(d) Each transaction entered into and closed on that day;  

(e) The unsettled balance at the beginning and end of the account on the transaction day, as well as all changes to the account balance during the day;  

(f) Details of all income credited and fees charged on that day
